Author: garbowza
Content:
I like the idea alot. I do have concerns on privacy and questions about how the whole process is simplified, however I have no doubt that Paul et al have implemented some clever techniques to handle all of this.

Looking forward to trying it out!

Author: nanijoe
Content:
Hmm..Do I really want my friends to have this much information about me? Do I really want ALL my friends to know that I spent 2 hours over the weekend (not working, but) checking out videos of buffy 'the body' on youtube? I find the updates on facebook mildly annoying, but this friendfeed thing is truly scary. What happens when your boss requests to be on your friendfeed? or your wife, or girlfriend, or mother or not-quite-best-friend? Saying yes or no could significantly alter that relationship for ever.

I wish you well Paul, but I hope you don't put us all in trouble.
